This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and neural networks, which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of pretrained embeddings and weight initialization, which are topics related to machine learning and deep learning, falling under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses attention-based models, which are commonly used in computer vision, falling under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of WordNet, which is a lexical database, and the use of embeddings in general, which are topics related to computational linguistics, falling under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
